---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Tulsa 1921 — The Destruction of Black Wall Street
description: On June 1, 1921, white mobs backed by government officials burned 35 blocks of the wealthiest Black community in America. At least 300 people were killed. No one was ever charged. The city buried the event for 80 years.
permalink: /tulsa/
---

<section class="hero hero--short" id="chapter-intro" data-chapter="Tulsa">
  <div class="hero__content">
    <span class="eyebrow">June 1, 1921</span>
    <h1 class="headline-hero hero__title">Black Wall Street</h1>
    <p class="subheadline hero__subtitle">
      35 blocks burned. 300 dead. 10,000 displaced. The city buried it for 80 years.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

